            </rs>. The Evidences against the Prisoner were 3 Soldiers who deposed, That they being drinking in a Cellar near Charing-Cross on the <rs id="t17180423-39-cd206" type="crimeDate">2d of March</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17180423-39-off205 t17180423-39-cd206"></join>, the Prisoner was there, who amidst a great deal of Swearing and Cursing, and disrespectful Words of King George, told them he wore better Cloth than the King's Soldiers, and taking up the Pot said, Here is a Health to King James the IIId . And they finding Fault with his proceedings, he call'd for a fresh Pot, and said to them, in spight of you, Here is a Health to King James the IIId, God bless him. That they told him they should be obliged to secure him, he told them he did not value them. There was Health to King James the IIId, God bless him. The Jury found him <rs id="t17180423-39-verdict207" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17180423-39-verdict207" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of the Misdemeanor, and he was <rs id="t17180423-39-punish208" type="punishmentDescription">
